description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a highly motivated consultant to join our growing team within&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Clinical Haematology service is hosted by Oldham Care Organisation. The directorate provides a full range of diagnostic and treatment services for haematological malignancies at British Committee for Standards in Haematology Level 2b. It also investigates and manages patients with a range of non- malignant haematological disorders directly and offers a consultative service to other clinical colleagues.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service includes a Cancer Standards Higher Intensity Chemotherapy inpatient facility (22 beds) and a day case facility centralised on the Oldham site. The unit provides both elective and non-elective capacity, including provision of chemotherapy and diagnostics.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Haematology provides 16 outpatient clinics per week across 3 hospital sites, comprising new and follow up outpatient assessment and treatments for a range of haematological conditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be an integral part of the team working alongside an experienced team of Consultants and junior medical staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Haematology service is on an improvement journey and has recently implemented a range of service improvements to benefit our patients, carers and staff. We are looking for an individual with vision and drive to deliver further improvements to our services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you on-going development to further enhance your skills and knowledge within a supportive environment. We are keen to work with individuals on their specific training needs and will aim to personalise job plans where possible to ensure that your own personal needs are met. Our Trust is proud to support you in continuing your professional development and you will continue to be supported for you annual appraisal and revalidation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Allameddine Allameddine  Consultant Haematology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email:  Allameddine.Allameddine@pat.nhs.uk  &lt;/p&gt;
